                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/405b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-08T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 8, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>984. Our 979, April 7, midnight. The British Embassy here has now informed us
                    that Alba apparently had no authority for putting forward the proposal outlined
                    in our telegram under reference. If that be the case of course the proposition
                    in our 936, April 4, 8 p.m. still holds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
